text: The 2010 New Mexico State Aggies football team represented New Mexico State University in the 2010 NCAA Division I FBS college football season. The Aggies were led by second–year head coach DeWayne Walker. They played their home games at Aggie Memorial Stadium and are members of the Western Athletic Conference. They finished the season 2–10, 1–7 in WAC play. ==Schedule== ==NFL Draft== 4th Round, 131 Overall Pick by the Green Bay Packers—Sr. CB Davon House ==References== ==External links== * New Mexico State - official site * NMState.com - official athletics site New Mexico State Category:New Mexico State Aggies football seasons Category:2010 in sports in New Mexico
